# Nanoplasm

NanoPlasm is a workflow dedicated to plasmid sequences assembly, typing and analysis based on long reads (Nanopore/PacBio).

The tool is still under active development.

sfsdfs

## Requirements

Some dependencies have to be installed for running NanoPlasm. It is highly advised to install them in a dedicated environment. Here is showed how to do it through conda:  
conda create -n nanoplasm  
conda install snakemake  
conda install bwa

![Nanoplasm_worflow](./misc/NanoPlasm.png)

